kona
------------------------------------------
Kona is the open-source implementation of the k3 programming language. k is a
synthesis of APL and LISP. Although many of the capabilities come from APL, the
fundamental data construct is quite different. In APL the construct is a
multi-dimensional matrix-like array, where the dimension of the array can range
from 0 to some maximum (often 9). In k, like LISP, the fundamental data
construct is a list. Also, like LISP, the k language is ASCII-based, so you
don't need a special keyboard.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.38-1
  cygport-0.35.1-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/kevinlawler/kona

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/kevinlawler/kona/archive/refs/tags/Win64-20211225.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack kona-20211225-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./kona-20211225-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/kona-20211225-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/kona-20211225-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(kona)
  /usr/bin/k.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/kona.README
  /usr/share/doc/kona/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/kona/README.md

